@startuml event-flow
title Event-Sourced Settlement Command Flow

actor Client
participant "Command Handler" as CH
participant "Aggregate" as AGG
participant "Marten Event Store" as ES
participant "Outbox Processor" as OP
participant "RabbitMQ" as RMQ

Client -> CH: Sends settlement command (Command ID)
activate CH
CH -> ES: Check idempotency (Command ID)
CH -> ES: Rehydrate Aggregate stream
ES --> CH: Current Aggregate state
CH -> AGG: Execute action (validate invariants)
activate AGG
AGG --> CH: List of Domain Events
deactivate AGG

CH -> ES: Transaction: Append events & Update projection
note over ES: Snapshotting mechanism used periodically\nto reduce rehydration time
ES --> CH: Success
CH --> Client: Command acknowledged (202 Accepted)
deactivate CH

OP -> ES: Scan for unprocessed outbox events
activate OP
OP -> RMQ: Publish events (At-least-once delivery)
activate RMQ
RMQ --> OP: ACK
deactivate RMQ
OP -> ES: Mark outbox events as published
deactivate OP

@enduml
